<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="commitment-n">commitment <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kə'mɪtmənt/    美 /kə'mɪtmənt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 投入；奉献</strong></h4>
<p>being prepared to give a lot of your time and attention to sth because you believe it is right or important：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A career as an actor requires one hundred percent commitment. 
演员这一行需要百分之百的投入。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 承诺；许诺；保证</strong></h4>
<p>a promise or agreement to do sth; a responsibility：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has <strong>made a commitment to going</strong> bottle free. 
她承诺不饮用瓶装水。</p><footer>2008 湖北</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-c">3.★ <strong>[C] 承诺的事 / 责任：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’m overworked at the moment — I’ve taken on too many commitments.
我目前劳累过度，承担的事情太多了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Giving up my job to go back to full-time education was a big <strong><em>_</em></strong>_, but now I know it was the best decision I ever made.  （2011 湖北）<br />
A.project<br />
B.commitment<br />
C.competition<br />
D.ambition  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. B  </p></div>